\pard\plain\s4\ql\sb240\sa120\keepn\f0\b\fs32\sl240\slmult1 \sb120 \fi0 1.1  A Warning or Two\par
\pard\plain\s0\qj\widctlpar\f0\fs22\sl240\slmult1 \sb60 \fi0 If you get too much space after a mid-sentence period\emdash abbreviations like etc. are the common culprits)\emdash then type a backslash followed by a space after the period, as in this sentence.\par
\pard\plain\s0\qj\widctlpar\f0\fs22\sl240\slmult1 \fi340 Remember, don\rquote t type the 10 special characters (such as dollar sign and backslash) except as directed!  The following seven are printed by typing a backslash in front of them: $ & # % _ \{ and \}. The manual tells how to make other symbols.\par
