\pard\plain\s0\qj\widctlpar\f0\fs22\sl240\slmult1 \sb60 \fi0 Because {\plain L{\up5\fs18 A}T{\dn7 E}X}{} will almost always convert a sequence of spaces into a single space, it can be rather difficult to lay out tables. See what happens in this example  {{\par
